<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<topic id="6cad4ea6-b7ab-4aae-a2a5-514a10b6fc34" revisionNumber="1">
  <developerConceptualDocument xmlns="http://ddue.schemas.microsoft.com/authoring/2003/5" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
    <introduction>
      <para>
        You can find several samples in the distribution package: a standalone setup, an all-in-one packaged setup and a demo of 
        component operators and several other examples of configuration files.
      </para>
    </introduction>
    <section address="standalonesetupsample">
      <title>Standalone Setup Sample</title>
      <content>
        <para>
          The Standalone setup is configured to correctly install the following components:
          <list class="bullet">
            <listItem>MDAC 2.8</listItem>
            <listItem>Jet 4.0 Sp8</listItem>
            <listItem>.NET Framework 1.1</listItem>
            <listItem>Your custom setup or windows installer package</listItem>
          </list>
          on these operating systems:
          <list class="bullet">
            <listItem>Windows XP</listItem>
            <listItem>Windows Server 2003</listItem>
          </list>
          The configuration files also check and install all the required software.
        </para>
        <para>
          You will find configuration files for English and Italian operating system.
        </para>
      </content>
    </section>
    <section address="standalonesetupsample">
      <title>Packaged Setup Sample</title>
      <content>
        <para>
          A working packaged setup, compiled with <application>InstallerLinker</application> into a 
          single Setup.exe with all its dependencies, including a simple MSI setup package.
        </para>
      </content>
    </section>
    <section address="operatorssample">
      <title>Component Operators Sample</title>
      <content>
        <para>
          A demo configuration of component operators. Shows how logical functions can be applied to install checks.
        </para>
      </content>
    </section>
    <section address="downloadsetupsample">
      <title>Download Setup Sample</title>
      <content>
        <para>
          A demo configuration of downloadable components.
        </para>
      </content>
    </section>
    <section address="installcheckproductsample">
      <title>Install Check Product Sample</title>
      <content>
        <para>
          A demo configuration of product installed checks that use the MSI database to lookup previously installed
          products or products related by UpgradeCode.
        </para>
      </content>
    </section>
    <section address="osfilterssample">
      <title>Operating System Filters Sample</title>
      <content>
        <para>
          A demo configuration that installs MSI 4.5 on three ranges of operating systems. Also demonstrates the
          'msu' Windows Update component on Windows Vista.
        </para>
      </content>
    </section>
    <section address="referecesetupsample">
      <title>Reference Setup Sample</title>
      <content>
        <para>
          A demo configuration with multiple web-based reference setups.
        </para>
      </content>
    </section>
    <section address="custominputsetupsample">
      <title>Custom Input Setup Sample</title>
      <content>
        <para>
          A demo configuration with user-defined controls. It prompts for an additional directory used in a <literal>command</literal>
          component and has a checkbox that can make setup succeed or fail.
        </para>
      </content>
    </section>
  </developerConceptualDocument>
</topic>